In-Demand in New Jersey This Computer Networking Specialist program provides students the opportunity to become proficient in Windows, Linux and Cisco based systems, networking, cloud computing and Cyber Security. Students study administration, support and maintenance of local area networks both through using Microsoft Windows, Linux and Cisco networking systems, software and cloud based. This program prepares students for career opportunities in the computer-networking field as network specialist, administrator, support specialist, cloud and cyber security. This diploma program cover many CompTIA, Microsoft, Cisco, AWS, EC-Council & Linux Certifications preparation as like: A+, Network+, Security+, CySA+/CND, CEH, MCP, MCA/MCE, CCNA, Linux+ and AWS certifications. In-Demand in New Jersey The Cyber Security Specialist Certificate provides both technical and strategic knowledge to help you fully leverage innovations while moving your organization from a reactive to a predictive approach to risk mitigation. NJ Department of Labor and Workforce Development Center for Occupational Employment Information (COEI) PO Box 057, 5th Floor, Trenton, New Jersey 08625-0057 My Career NJ User Sign-Up Form Sign up for emails to learn about tools and resources to help you advance your career. Read about our privacy policy . LasComp Institute of IT This training may be eligible for funding from your One-Stop Career Center. In-Demand in New Jersey This package cover following three CompTIA certifications: A+, Network+ & MCP. * CompTIA A+ confirms a technician's ability to perform tasks such as installation, configuration, diagnosing, preventive maintenance and basic networking. The exams also cover domains such as security, safety and environmental issues and communication and professionalism. * CompTIA Network+ validates the knowledge and skills of networking professionals. It is an international, vendor-neutral certification that recognizes a technician's ability to describe the features and functions of networking components and to install, configure and troubleshoot basic networking hardware, protocols and services. * Microsoft Certified Professional Windows Client: In this course, students learn how to install, upgrade, and migrate to Windows Client O/S. Students then configure Windows client for network connectivity, security, maintenance, and mobile computing.
